 demonstrated a\nsignificant upregulation of osteogenic-related genes for the scaffolds\npreviously immersed in PBS when compared to the as-printed PVA-containing\nscaffolds. Although the pre-immersion scaffolds performed equally towards\nosteogenic cell differentiation, our data suggest that a short immersion in PBS\nof MBG scaffolds is beneficial for the osteogenic properties and might\naccelerate bone formation after implantation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Mar 2021 19:01:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-23"}
